# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithMage1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Behind her, there was only a hole in the wall where she had come from."
    new "Behind her, there was only a hole in the wall where she had come from."

    old "As her eyes narrowed, she saw a soft glimmer in the air in front of it."
    new "As her eyes narrowed, she saw a soft glimmer in the air in front of it."

    old "Reaching out with her hand, she could feel it give way, like a door slightly opening to the touch."
    new "Reaching out with her hand, she could feel it give way, like a door slightly opening to the touch."

    old "She pulled back her hand."
    new "She pulled back her hand."

    old "Ever since she had come to study with Xan, she had relied on him for guidance."
    new "Ever since she had come to study with Xan, she had relied on him for guidance."

    old "So much of the magical world was still strange to her. She imitated him, hoping it would be enough."
    new "So much of the magical world was still strange to her. She imitated him, hoping it would be enough."

    old "Sarah traced her hand across the floor of the ruined house she was standing in."
    new "Sarah traced her hand across the floor of the ruined house she was standing in."

    old "She had no idea how big this place was, and she wanted to be sure she could find her way back."
    new "She had no idea how big this place was, and she wanted to be sure she could find her way back."

    old "Leaving a small trace of magical energy, she would have no trouble telling this house apart from all the others."
    new "Leaving a small trace of magical energy, she would have no trouble telling this house apart from all the others."

    old "Looking up, Sarah saw that the roof of the house had collapsed."
    new "Looking up, Sarah saw that the roof of the house had collapsed."

    old "Instead of a ceiling, she could look right up to the sky, filled with stars."
    new "Instead of a ceiling, she could look right up to the sky, filled with stars."

    old "They somehow seemed brighter here than in Lethram."
    new "They somehow seemed brighter here than in Lethram."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah felt something pulling on her."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah felt something pulling on her."

    old "Her fingers moved across her chest, grasping for something she couldn't see."
    new "Her fingers moved across her chest, grasping for something she couldn't see."

    old "Around her, only the abandoned ruin of the house. Nothing else."
    new "Around her, only the abandoned ruin of the house. Nothing else."

    old "And still..."
    new "And still..."

    old "Still she felt something acting on her. Drawing her."
    new "Still she felt something acting on her. Drawing her."

    old "She knew it the way a child might know to reach for its mother."
    new "She knew it the way a child might know to reach for its mother."

    old "Sarah stepped out of the ruined house, in the direction she felt drawn to."
    new "Sarah stepped out of the ruined house, in the direction she felt drawn to."

    old "Stepping out of the house and onto the street, Sarah first laid her eyes on the city of Nauyziri proper."
    new "Stepping out of the house and onto the street, Sarah first laid her eyes on the city of Nauyziri proper."

    old "The whole thing was a ruin."
    new "The whole thing was a ruin."

    old "Everywhere she looked, signs of decay. Even the road itself was broken."
    new "Everywhere she looked, signs of decay. Even the road itself was broken."

    old "Sand from the desert danced through the streets."
    new "Sand from the desert danced through the streets."

    old "This was the edge of the world. Far beyond where any life still thrived."
    new "This was the edge of the world. Far beyond where any life still thrived."

    old "For a brief moment, she could imagine herself all alone on the world."
    new "For a brief moment, she could imagine herself all alone on the world."

    old "Then her eyes were drawn towards the center of the city, a fair distance away from her."
    new "Then her eyes were drawn towards the center of the city, a fair distance away from her."

    old "Light."
    new "Light."

    old "It took her a moment to understand. Campfires."
    new "It took her a moment to understand. Campfires."

    old "Not just a few, but a great many."
    new "Not just a few, but a great many."

    old "Crawling around in the twilight of the night and the fires, countless people swarming around."
    new "Crawling around in the twilight of the night and the fires, countless people swarming around."

    old "Nothing could live here, but the more she studied them from afar, the more Sarah understood."
    new "Nothing could live here, but the more she studied them from afar, the more Sarah understood."

    old "It was an army."
    new "It was an army."

    old "Mythran by the looks of it. But she spotted a few other banners among them too."
    new "Mythran by the looks of it. But she spotted a few other banners among them too."

    old "What reason could a Mythran legion have for being out here?"
    new "What reason could a Mythran legion have for being out here?"

    old "Sarah couldn't imagine a reason. Then again, the Mythran empire was never known for being transparent."
    new "Sarah couldn't imagine a reason. Then again, the Mythran empire was never known for being transparent."

    old "She continued to feel whatever force it was, pulling on her."
    new "She continued to feel whatever force it was, pulling on her."

    old "Keeping an eye on the crowd of soldiers, Sarah began to walk."
    new "Keeping an eye on the crowd of soldiers, Sarah began to walk."

    old "She wasn't sure why they were here, or even if they'd harm her. All she knew was that she didn't want to risk finding out one way to the other."
    new "She wasn't sure why they were here, or even if they'd harm her. All she knew was that she didn't want to risk finding out one way to the other."

    old "Sarah made her way up the road, doing her best to avoid anyone."
    new "Sarah made her way up the road, doing her best to avoid anyone."

    old "Whatever the force was, it continued to guide her."
    new "Whatever the force was, it continued to guide her."

    old "Sarah hoped to avoid most of the soldiers, but the thing was pulling her closer to the center of the city."
    new "Sarah hoped to avoid most of the soldiers, but the thing was pulling her closer to the center of the city."

    old "The core of the army was camped out in the lower parts of the city, but slowly the streets were getting busier."
    new "The core of the army was camped out in the lower parts of the city, but slowly the streets were getting busier."

    old "She avoided the first few soldiers she ran into, but over time, she found more and more wandering about."
    new "She avoided the first few soldiers she ran into, but over time, she found more and more wandering about."

    old "One moment, she slipped up, and a soldier came stumbling out of a house."
    new "One moment, she slipped up, and a soldier came stumbling out of a house."

    old "Sarah felt her heart race, but whatever disaster she imagined, never came."
    new "Sarah felt her heart race, but whatever disaster she imagined, never came."

    old "The soldier eyed her, wobbled from side to side, then stumbled away."
    new "The soldier eyed her, wobbled from side to side, then stumbled away."

    old "As Sarah watched him leave, it was clear he was drunk."
    new "As Sarah watched him leave, it was clear he was drunk."

    old "Sarah continued walking along the road when she suddenly heard a voice."
    new "Sarah continued walking along the road when she suddenly heard a voice."

    old "Ssss..a..araah..."
    new "Ssss..a..araah..."

    old "Though it was slurred beyond comprehension, the voice was familiar enough to her that she knew who it was."
    new "Though it was slurred beyond comprehension, the voice was familiar enough to her that she knew who it was."

    old "Sarah turned towards the voice and saw Kate."
    new "Sarah turned towards the voice and saw Kate."

    old "Kate was sitting, slouched up against a wall. Her head slightly hanging to her side."
    new "Kate was sitting, slouched up against a wall. Her head slightly hanging to her side."

    old "Sarah saw the bottle near her, though judging by Kate's appearance, she doubted it had just been the one bottle."
    new "Sarah saw the bottle near her, though judging by Kate's appearance, she doubted it had just been the one bottle."

    old "She slowly walked closer."
    new "She slowly walked closer."

    old "Fu...fuck me...am I this deep in...already?"
    new "Fu...fuck me...am I this deep in...already?"

    old "She saw Kate's eyes drifting, unfocussed, from side to side."
    new "She saw Kate's eyes drifting, unfocussed, from side to side."

    old "Sarah wasn't all that close, and still she could smell the alcohol."
    new "Sarah wasn't all that close, and still she could smell the alcohol."

    old "It was heavy on the air. A stench unlike any other."
    new "It was heavy on the air. A stench unlike any other."

    old "She looked down at Kate with pity."
    new "She looked down at Kate with pity."

    old "Sarah couldn't deny that she was surprised to see Kate here, out on the edge of the world."
    new "Sarah couldn't deny that she was surprised to see Kate here, out on the edge of the world."

    old "But she was more surprised by how little she seemed to care."
    new "But she was more surprised by how little she seemed to care."

    old "Her old friend. Her oldest friend, once."
    new "Her old friend. Her oldest friend, once."

    old "On a cold and clinical level, Sarah imagined that she should help Kate. But there was no friendship here."
    new "On a cold and clinical level, Sarah imagined that she should help Kate. But there was no friendship here."

    old "Is...really you?"
    new "Is...really you?"

    old "Yes, Kate. It's really me."
    new "Yes, Kate. It's really me."

    old "You...why...what are you..."
    new "You...why...what are you..."

    old "Don't worry yourself about me. You look like a mess."
    new "Don't worry yourself about me. You look like a mess."

    old "She might once have picked her words more carefully. By now, she simply said it like it was."
    new "She might once have picked her words more carefully. By now, she simply said it like it was."

    old "An apology? Sarah hadn't expected that."
    new "An apology? Sarah hadn't expected that."

    old "Sorry that...I'm a fuckin...mess...cause my friend is dead...cause of you..."
    new "Sorry that...I'm a fuckin...mess...cause my friend is dead...cause of you..."

    old "Her friend?"
    new "Her friend?"

    old "Sarah searched her mind, when she remembered the boy. Caleb, was it."
    new "Sarah searched her mind, when she remembered the boy. Caleb, was it."

    old "She'd met him years ago, but he had stormed the throne room. It was war. Did the boy not come with the same intent to murder?"
    new "She'd met him years ago, but he had stormed the throne room. It was war. Did the boy not come with the same intent to murder?"

    old "Aah, I see. It's my fault that you're this way. Convenient."
    new "Aah, I see. It's my fault that you're this way. Convenient."

    old "She saw Kate begin to sob, uncontrollable, the way drunkards liked to do. Full of self pity."
    new "She saw Kate begin to sob, uncontrollable, the way drunkards liked to do. Full of self pity."

    old "Rather than solicit empathy, Sarah only felt disgust."
    new "Rather than solicit empathy, Sarah only felt disgust."

    old "You...you never looked for me...you..."
    new "You...you never looked for me...you..."

    old "Get off it, Kate."
    new "Get off it, Kate."

    old "Sarah's words came hard and fast."
    new "Sarah's words came hard and fast."

    old "I won't pretend your life was easy, but mine hasn't been easy either."
    new "I won't pretend your life was easy, but mine hasn't been easy either."

    old "You don't think I have a thousand excuses to drink myself to death in a ditch somewhere?"
    new "You don't think I have a thousand excuses to drink myself to death in a ditch somewhere?"

    old "You want to stack up grievance and tragedies, see who comes out the winner?"
    new "You want to stack up grievance and tragedies, see who comes out the winner?"

    old "Sarah watched as Kate threw back another drink."
    new "Sarah watched as Kate threw back another drink."

    old "The wine poured down Kate's throat so fast; Sarah doubted that Kate even tasted any of it."
    new "The wine poured down Kate's throat so fast; Sarah doubted that Kate even tasted any of it."

    old "Then again, taste was hardly the point."
    new "Then again, taste was hardly the point."

    old "Fuck you..."
    new "Fuck you..."

    old "Sarah watched as Kate stumbled onto her feet. Nearly falling several times as she tried."
    new "Sarah watched as Kate stumbled onto her feet. Nearly falling several times as she tried."

    old "Kate reached to her hip and clumsily pulled her blade from its sheath."
    new "Kate reached to her hip and clumsily pulled her blade from its sheath."

    old "Two steps forward."
    new "Two steps forward."

    old "Sarah breathed in air and breathed out magic."
    new "Sarah breathed in air and breathed out magic."

    old "It was so simple, it barely counted as a spell. But it was enough."
    new "It was so simple, it barely counted as a spell. But it was enough."

    old "The gust of air produced by her magic, threw up the sands and knocked Kate backwards."
    new "The gust of air produced by her magic, threw up the sands and knocked Kate backwards."

    old "Had she even remotely been ready, or sober, she likely could have remained on her feet, but she was neither, and so Kate fell back."
    new "Had she even remotely been ready, or sober, she likely could have remained on her feet, but she was neither, and so Kate fell back."

    old "Her sword slipped from her hand and fell a few feet from her."
    new "Her sword slipped from her hand and fell a few feet from her."

    old "Sarah watched, expecting Kate to get back up. Instead, Kate simply staid on the ground."
    new "Sarah watched, expecting Kate to get back up. Instead, Kate simply staid on the ground."

    old "Her body rocked as she began to sob again."
    new "Her body rocked as she began to sob again."

    old "She could kill Kate with ease, but what would even be the point? The truth was that after their last encounter, whatever had remained between them was gone."
    new "She could kill Kate with ease, but what would even be the point? The truth was that after their last encounter, whatever had remained between them was gone."

    old "Not friendship. Not love. Not hatred."
    new "Not friendship. Not love. Not hatred."

    old "Only nothingness. Just a stranger that seemed too familiar."
    new "Only nothingness. Just a stranger that seemed too familiar."

    old "Goodbye, Kate. I really do hope you'll get better."
    new "Goodbye, Kate. I really do hope you'll get better."

    old "It was a hollow wish."
    new "It was a hollow wish."

    old "She left Kate behind her, and Kate could not follow."
    new "She left Kate behind her, and Kate could not follow."

    old "Not long after the soldier stumbled out of sight, a woman came out of the ruined house."
    new "Not long after the soldier stumbled out of sight, a woman came out of the ruined house."

    old "She straightened out her clothes. A servant, or a slave perhaps, judging by her appearance."
    new "She straightened out her clothes. A servant, or a slave perhaps, judging by her appearance."

    old "She gave Sarah a brief look, then made her way down the road."
    new "She gave Sarah a brief look, then made her way down the road."

    old "If anything, Sarah thought, the woman looked more embarassed than shocked to see her."
    new "If anything, Sarah thought, the woman looked more embarassed than shocked to see her."

    old "Slowly, Sarah began to realize that with an army this large, it was likely that many of them might have no idea whether she belonged or didn't."
    new "Slowly, Sarah began to realize that with an army this large, it was likely that many of them might have no idea whether she belonged or didn't."

    old "And out here, she was just one woman."
    new "And out here, she was just one woman."

    old "How much damage could one woman really do?"
    new "How much damage could one woman really do?"

    old "With her powers, more than enough, but they didn't need to know that."
    new "With her powers, more than enough, but they didn't need to know that."

    old "Confident that there was little risk, and eager to discover the source of whichever acted on her, Sarah began to walk faster."
    new "Confident that there was little risk, and eager to discover the source of whichever acted on her, Sarah began to walk faster."

    old "She passed by more soldiers."
    new "She passed by more soldiers."

    old "Sarah simply pretended that she belonged, and the soldiers for their part either believed or didn't care."
    new "Sarah simply pretended that she belonged, and the soldiers for their part either believed or didn't care."

    old "As she made her way to the top of the road, she suddenly found the city opening up before her."
    new "As she made her way to the top of the road, she suddenly found the city opening up before her."

    old "For a brief moment, her mind raced trying to understand what she was even really looking at."
    new "For a brief moment, her mind raced trying to understand what she was even really looking at."

    old "Then it came into focus."
    new "Then it came into focus."

    old "A massive hole had been dug straight into the earth."
    new "A massive hole had been dug straight into the earth."

    old "Scaffolding was put up along the sides of the pit, making it seem almost like a mining camp."
    new "Scaffolding was put up along the sides of the pit, making it seem almost like a mining camp."

    old "As Sarah walked closer, she could see the construction more clearly, and she realized what it was."
    new "As Sarah walked closer, she could see the construction more clearly, and she realized what it was."

    old "An archeological digsite."
    new "An archeological digsite."

    old "It explained, though perhaps in part, what the Mythrans were doing here."
    new "It explained, though perhaps in part, what the Mythrans were doing here."

    old "A few men and women dressed in the robes of scholars were walking around the digsite, but they seemed equally uninterested in her."
    new "A few men and women dressed in the robes of scholars were walking around the digsite, but they seemed equally uninterested in her."

    old "Sarah came up to the ledge."
    new "Sarah came up to the ledge."

    old "Looking down, she could see the lowest point in the quarry."
    new "Looking down, she could see the lowest point in the quarry."

    old "Whichever pulled on her, was never stronger than now."
    new "Whichever pulled on her, was never stronger than now."

    old "She had never been to this place before, and yet every step she took felt obvious."
    new "She had never been to this place before, and yet every step she took felt obvious."

    old "Even the last one."
    new "Even the last one."

    old "Sarah realized she was falling, only when it was too late."
    new "Sarah realized she was falling, only when it was too late."

    old "But as the earth rushed up towards her, she wondered only why her heart was so calm."
    new "But as the earth rushed up towards her, she wondered only why her heart was so calm."

    old "The space is surprisingly soundless, only the sound of rocks scratching against her leather boots can be heard."
    new "The space is surprisingly soundless, only the sound of rocks scratching against her leather boots can be heard."

    old "Suddenly, the sounds of grinding rock vanish, and she hears her own footsteps being muted."
    new "Suddenly, the sounds of grinding rock vanish, and she hears her own footsteps being muted."

    old "Sarah takes off one of her gloves and places her hands against the grass."
    new "Sarah takes off one of her gloves and places her hands against the grass."

    old "Finally, we meet face to face, Sarah. The real me."
    new "Finally, we meet face to face, Sarah. The real me."

    old "Razaphel?"
    new "Razaphel?"

    old "She speaks the name softly, as if fearing the response."
    new "She speaks the name softly, as if fearing the response."

    old "The last of it to take shape, the familiar face-mask."
    new "The last of it to take shape, the familiar face-mask."

    old "Sarah watches as Razaphel's form takes hold."
    new "Sarah watches as Razaphel's form takes hold."

    old "It was the spirit, unmistakably, only larger."
    new "It was the spirit, unmistakably, only larger."

    old "What is this? More tricks?"
    new "What is this? More tricks?"

    old "She heard the spirit hiss, its voice echoing in the hollowed out space."
    new "She heard the spirit hiss, its voice echoing in the hollowed out space."

    old "No, Sarah. No more tricks."
    new "No, Sarah. No more tricks."

    old "What then? You've lured me out here, to the edge of the world...for what?"
    new "What then? You've lured me out here, to the edge of the world...for what?"

    old "She had found the spirit to be a useful ally, but she was quickly losing her patience with the creature."
    new "She had found the spirit to be a useful ally, but she was quickly losing her patience with the creature."

    old "Before this moment, we had not ever truly met."
    new "Before this moment, we had not ever truly met."

    old "She watched Razaphel's body continue to twist and move through the open space."
    new "She watched Razaphel's body continue to twist and move through the open space."

    old "Its body seemed to cling to the black monolith object that sat at the center of the room."
    new "Its body seemed to cling to the black monolith object that sat at the center of the room."

    old "Tell me what you mean."
    new "Tell me what you mean."

    old "It paused before speaking."
    new "It paused before speaking."

    old "This is my true form. The other spaces in which we met...the mage's house...Bagrad...only echoes of myself."
    new "This is my true form. The other spaces in which we met...the mage's house...Bagrad...only echoes of myself."

    old "Echoes?"
    new "Echoes?"

    old "Suppose you were to fill up a cup with water and then pierced the bottom with a knife, several times."
    new "Suppose you were to fill up a cup with water and then pierced the bottom with a knife, several times."

    old "The water would pour out from different places, but it would all be the same water."
    new "The water would pour out from different places, but it would all be the same water."

    old "This place here is my source."
    new "This place here is my source."

    old "Sarah looked past the spirit's body, towards the black monolith."
    new "Sarah looked past the spirit's body, towards the black monolith."

    old "She gestured at it."
    new "She gestured at it."

    old "And that?"
    new "And that?"

    old "Perceptive."
    new "Perceptive."

    old "The spirit's voice was like a hoarse whisper."
    new "The spirit's voice was like a hoarse whisper."

    old "Sarah grew annoyed."
    new "Sarah grew annoyed."

    old "Give me answers or I will leave, Razaphel. You promised me truth, I won't stand your riddles again."
    new "Give me answers or I will leave, Razaphel. You promised me truth, I won't stand your riddles again."

    old "Very well. Let us speak only truth then."
    new "Very well. Let us speak only truth then."

    old "Razaphel's body spun around the monolith. Its body like vapor."
    new "Razaphel's body spun around the monolith. Its body like vapor."

    old "You know of how my kind came about in your world, do you not?"
    new "You know of how my kind came about in your world, do you not?"

    old "Sarah did know. Xan had told her a long time ago."
    new "Sarah did know. Xan had told her a long time ago."

    old "An arrogant Empress. A failed ritual. Worlds colliding."
    new "An arrogant Empress. A failed ritual. Worlds colliding."

    old "Empress Ayamari summoned your world into ours."
    new "Empress Ayamari summoned your world into ours."

    old "She did. Millenia ago."
    new "She did. Millenia ago."

    old "But did the mage ever tell you why?"
    new "But did the mage ever tell you why?"

    old "Sarah searched her mind."
    new "Sarah searched her mind."

    old "Yes...she wanted to be immortal. To live forever."
    new "Yes...she wanted to be immortal. To live forever."

    old "The spirit hissed again."
    new "The spirit hissed again."

    old "So it was, but that does not answer the question of why."
    new "So it was, but that does not answer the question of why."

    old "Why what?"
    new "Why what?"

    old "Why my world."
    new "Why my world."

    old "Sarah admitted that she had never given that part of the history much concern."
    new "Sarah admitted that she had never given that part of the history much concern."

    old "I suppose...I don't know."
    new "I suppose...I don't know."

    old "Sarah watched as Razaphel drifted closer towards her, slowly."
    new "Sarah watched as Razaphel drifted closer towards her, slowly."

    old "Once she had been frightened by the creature, but over time, she had more pitied it."
    new "Once she had been frightened by the creature, but over time, she had more pitied it."

    old "Perhaps that was dangerous as well, she thought. She didn't truly know the spirit or its intentions."
    new "Perhaps that was dangerous as well, she thought. She didn't truly know the spirit or its intentions."

    old "Gods are the spark that begin the birth of a world, but they are equally of that world."
    new "Gods are the spark that begin the birth of a world, but they are equally of that world."

    old "There is a cyclical nature to they who create, and are in turn birthed from their own creation."
    new "There is a cyclical nature to they who create, and are in turn birthed from their own creation."

    old "And like all craftsmen, they pour their own selves into their works."
    new "And like all craftsmen, they pour their own selves into their works."

    old "She watched as the face mask drew nearer. Then lingered."
    new "She watched as the face mask drew nearer. Then lingered."

    old "You imagine your world to be the way all worlds are, but this is not true."
    new "You imagine your world to be the way all worlds are, but this is not true."

    old "In my world, there were not many Gods, but only three. They were called the Three Sisters."
    new "In my world, there were not many Gods, but only three. They were called the Three Sisters."

    old "Their divine mandate was one of growth and flourishing."
    new "Their divine mandate was one of growth and flourishing."

    old "True immortality in your world is rare, a gift the Gods jealously guard for themselves..."
    new "True immortality in your world is rare, a gift the Gods jealously guard for themselves..."

    old "But in my world, it was abundant. The Three Sisters gave it freely to all who desired it."
    new "But in my world, it was abundant. The Three Sisters gave it freely to all who desired it."

    old "There was no want. No famine. No disease. No age."
    new "There was no want. No famine. No disease. No age."

    old "All lived for as long as they wished, free to pursue their own desires."
    new "All lived for as long as they wished, free to pursue their own desires."

    old "Only when one was tired of life or had fulfilled all ambitions, did they freely go to the House of Dying."
    new "Only when one was tired of life or had fulfilled all ambitions, did they freely go to the House of Dying."

    old "There, the Three Sisters held court, and held sway over life and death."
    new "There, the Three Sisters held court, and held sway over life and death."

    old "It sounds like a paradise...how can such a thing even be?"
    new "It sounds like a paradise...how can such a thing even be?"

    old "Because the Gods make the world in the image that they are themselves. The Three Sisters desired only to see the growth of their garden."
    new "Because the Gods make the world in the image that they are themselves. The Three Sisters desired only to see the growth of their garden."

    old "Your Gods are a vast Pantheon, forever squabling among one another like children. Envious. Greedy."
    new "Your Gods are a vast Pantheon, forever squabling among one another like children. Envious. Greedy."

    old "The Pantheon of your Gods is a hierarchy of power. Those who sit at the top, and the many who sit at the bottom."
    new "The Pantheon of your Gods is a hierarchy of power. Those who sit at the top, and the many who sit at the bottom."

    old "And just like your Gods, your own world is made in their image."
    new "And just like your Gods, your own world is made in their image."

    old "That much, Sarah knew to be true. For every king and emperor in her world, there were millions who simply toiled away their lives."
    new "That much, Sarah knew to be true. For every king and emperor in her world, there were millions who simply toiled away their lives."

    old "The Empress reached out to my world for its abundance, and she imagined the Sisters would have gladly given her the everlasting life she desired."
    new "The Empress reached out to my world for its abundance, and she imagined the Sisters would have gladly given her the everlasting life she desired."

    old "But as you know, the nature of reality cannot tolerate the conjoining of worlds."
    new "But as you know, the nature of reality cannot tolerate the conjoining of worlds."

    old "My world as subsumed into yours, trapped beneath it."
    new "My world as subsumed into yours, trapped beneath it."

    old "Sarah nodded. This part too, she had heard."
    new "Sarah nodded. This part too, she had heard."

    old "And then your race invaded our world."
